  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the role of citizen science and local and indigenous knowledge in SDG planning and monitoring in the Caribbean</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the success of the Sandwatch network in the Caribbean, and UNESCO&apos;s global experience in Local and Indigenous knowledge systems (LINKS); activities will focus on raising national visibility of Sandwatch chapters, including in UNCTs; and promoting citizen science and local and indigenous knowledge as tools for SDG planning, DRR and baseline and impact assessments of disasters (PDNA). Some planned actions with youth groups in the English and Dutch Caribbean SIDS will contribute to the recently established Caribbean Youth Network on Climate Change, to increase youth-driven climate change action, integrating local and indigenous knowledge - where possible, taking advantage of previous/on-going Sandwatch activities.</narrative>
  </description>
